# Project Rules: React TypeScript App

> Single-Page Application built with React, TypeScript, and Vite.

## Project Identity

- **Type**: Web Frontend (SPA)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Framework**: React 18+ with Vite
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **State**: Zustand
- **Testing**: Vitest + React Testing Library

---

## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `UserProfile.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useAuth.ts` |
| Utils | camelCase | `formatDate.ts` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase with `I` or `T` prefix | `IUser`, `TApiResponse` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |
| Directories | kebab-case | `user-profile/` |

### File Organization

```
src/
├── components/     # Reusable UI components
│   └── Button/
│       ├── Button.tsx
│       ├── Button.test.tsx
│       └── index.ts
├── pages/          # Route-level components
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks
├── stores/         # Zustand stores
├── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
├── utils/          # Utility functions
└── services/       # API client functions
```

---

## Critical Rules (🔴)

### Rule 1: ❌ Never use `any`

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const fetchData = async (): Promise<any> => { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  data: T;
  status: number;
}
const fetchData = async (): Promise<ApiResponse<User[]>> => { ... }
```

### Rule 2: ✅ Always use functional components with hooks

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — class component
class UserList extends React.Component { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — functional with hooks
const UserList: React.FC = () => {
  const [users, setUsers] = useState<User[]>([]);
  // ...
};
```

---

## Important Guidelines (🟠)

- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Co-locate tests with components (`Component.test.tsx`)
- Use `React.memo()` only when profiling shows re-render issues
- Extract logic into custom hooks when a component exceeds 100 lines

---

## Code Smells to Avoid

| ❌ Smell | ✅ Instead Do |
|----------|--------------|
| Props drilling > 2 levels | Use Zustand store or Context |
| `useEffect` for derived state | Use `useMemo` |
| Inline styles | Use Tailwind classes |
| Giant component (> 200 lines) | Extract into smaller components + hooks |
